sources.title: Wuthering Heights (TV-1958) RICHARD BURTON
sources.description:
It's Friday@PizzaFLIX 
Stars: Richard Burton, Rosemary Harris, Patty Duke, Micheal Ray
Director:Daniel Petrie
Writer: Emily Brontë (based on a novel by)

Screen legend Richard Burton makes his US small screen debut as Heathcliff in Emily Brontë's Gothic love story. The object of obsession is played by Patty Duke as the young Catherine, and Rosemary Harris as the adult. 

TRIVIA: Long presumed lost, this live TV production of Wuthering Heights was first seen on the CBS network May 9th, 1958, as a 90-minute presentation of DuPont Show of the Month.
